                           *** How To Play ***

           Flasher II is an addictive and challenging game designed
           to test your memory.  Simply repeat an ever-increasing
           sequence of colors in order to score points.  

           At the Flasher directory, type FLASHER2 to begin the game.
           The program will check for a VGA card, mouse, and soundcard
           card.  If your system does not have a VGA card or mouse, the
           program will exit you back to DOS.  If your system does not
           have a soundcard, your sound options will be limited to the 
           PC speaker.  Flasher II uses the FM chip which is located in
           the same memory location on most (if not all) soundcards, so 
           if you have one, it should find it. (Hey, it works on MY 
           SoundBlaster...).

           Once all this is done, you will be prompted to click the mouse
           button to being the game. IT IS HIGHLY SUGGESTED THAT YOU RUN
           THIS GAME FROM YOUR HARD DRIVE.  RUNNING IT OFF OF A FLOPPY DISK 
           WILL TAKE A BIT LONGER WHILE THE PROGRAM READS THE DATA FILE.  
           However, all data is read into memory prior to the start of the
           game, so once it is done, game speed is not affected not matter
           where you run it from.

           The mouse is used to make your selections as well as flipping
           through the intro screens.  After the Caledonian Enterprises
           logo fades out, the title screen will appear and a few colors
           will be flashed.  Click the left mouse button to go through
           the other screens until you reach the main menu.

                              *** Main Menu ***

           The main menu screen consists of 5 options:

           PLAY GAME - Clicking this button will take you to the game
                       options menu (See Option Menu).

           INSTRUCTIONS - Clicking this button will take you to the 
                       instruction screens.  There are 15 pages of 
                       instructions explaining how to play the game, as
                       well as explaining the option settings.

           REGISTRATION - Clicking this button will take you to the 
                       registration screen.  Simple enough.

           HIGH SCORES - Clicking this button takes you to two screens.
                       The first screen shows the highscores for the 
                       normal game.  Click the left mouse button to see
                       the highscores for the phase game.

           QUIT -      This is easy enough to figure out, click this button
                       to exit the game.


                                 *** Option Menu ***

           The Option Menu consists of 7 options:

           LEVEL - This option sets the level of difficulty for the game.
                   There are three levels:

                   HARD - This causes the game to increase the sequence
                          of colors flashed by 3 colors at a time.  You
                          receive 300 points for each correct response.
                          (Registered users only!)

                   MEDIUM - This causes the game to increase the sequence
                          of colors flashed by 2 colors at a time.  You
                          receive 200 points for each correct response.
                          (Registered users only!)

                   EASY - This causes the game to increase the sequence of
                          colors flashed by 1 color at a time.  You receive
                          100 points for each correct response.

           PLAYERS - This option sets the number of players in the game.

           VARIANT - This option consists of 2 choices.

                   NORMAL - This option sets the game to 'normal' mode.
                          Normal mode basically sets the game to flashing
                          an ever-increasing sequence of colors.

                   PHASE - This option turns the game into more of a 
                          challenge.  You are forced to clear levels of
                          of increasing difficulty and longer sequences.
                          (Registered Users only!) 

           SOUND - There are 5 sound options here:

                   PC -   This option plays sound out of the PC Speaker.

                   SH -   Shhhh....  This turns off the sound in the game.

                   I -    (Soundcard users only) Sets the sound to  
                          Stereo Sound I.

                   II -   (Soundcard users only) Sets the sound to
                          Stereo Sound II.  (Registered Users only!)

                   III -  (Soundcard users only) Sets the sound to 
                          Stereo Sound III.  (Registered Users only!)

           SPEED - There are 3 speed settings for the game.  Select 1
                   for fast, 2 for normal, 3 for slow.

           START - Click this to begin playing Flasher II.  (See The 
                   Game Screen)

           MAIN MENU - Click this to go back to the Main Menu.


                             *** The Game Screen ***

           Selecting START from the Option Menu will take you to the
           game screen.  Each game lasts for 3 rounds.  The Round
           indicator will increment on each round.  There will be a 
           window on your screen which will read "PLAYER ONE  (Click to
           Start)".  Click your left mouse button to begin the game.

           The Status indicator will read "PAUSE" as it gets a new color or
           colors, depending on which level of difficulty you selected.
           Once done, it will display "WAIT" while it flashes the colors.
           When it reads "READY", you may begin to type in your response.

           The active keys are 1,2,3,4, and ESC.  The keys are in the same
           order as the colors on the screen:

                 BLUE = 1    RED = 2    YELLOW = 3    GREEN = 4

           Pressing ESC will cause a window to pop up asking you if you
           wish to exit the game.

           EXAMPLE:

               You are playing an EASY game (One color at a time).
               
               Red flashes on the screen.

               You press '2'. (Remember: RED = 2)

               You are correct and recieve 100 points.

               Then, red flashes again along with green.

               You press '2', then '4'. (RED = 2   GREEN = 4)

               Once again you are correct and recieve 200 more points (100
               points for each right response) for a total of 300 points.

               This will continue until you give a wrong response.

                           *** ABOUT FLASHER II ***

               Flasher II is a major improvement over the original 
               Flasher. The original FLasher was written in QBasic, 
               used text graphics and PC SPEAKER sound.  Flasher II 
               was written in BorlandC and Turbo Assembler, features 
               256-color VGA graphics, mouse support, and SoundBlaster 
               stereo sounds, as well as a host of user options.

               (QBasic is owned by Microsoft Corporation) 

               (BorlandC and Turbo Assembler are owned by Borland 
                International)
               
               (SoundBlaster is owned by Creative Labs)

               
